298
00:27:49,716 --> 00:27:51,445
Don't look at the camera. Go on. Keep going.

299
00:27:51,651 --> 00:27:53,642
All right, come on. Go.

300
00:27:59,059 --> 00:28:01,323
Yes. Over here. Over here.

301
00:28:15,742 --> 00:28:18,575
- Where can I find the CO?
- Can't miss him, sir. He's over there.

302
00:28:19,145 --> 00:28:21,613
Looking for a tank? I
got five tanks broken...

303
00:28:21,815 --> 00:28:25,148
We're all right with the
tanks. It's all right, captain.

304
00:28:25,352 --> 00:28:27,650
Captain Willard! I carry priority papers

305
00:28:27,854 --> 00:28:30,186
from COMSEC Intelligence II Corps.

306
00:28:30,390 --> 00:28:32,255
I understand Nha Trang has briefed you

307
00:28:32,459 --> 00:28:34,017
on the requirements of my mission.

308
00:28:34,227 --> 00:28:36,661
What mission? I haven't heard from Nha Trang.

309
00:28:36,863 --> 00:28:39,696
Sir, your unit is supposed
to escort us into the Nung.

310
00:28:39,899 --> 00:28:41,264
- We'll see what we can do,
- Colonel.

311
00:28:41,468 --> 00:28:44,699
But just stay out of my way
till this is done, captain.

312
00:28:49,442 --> 00:28:52,070
All right, let's see what we
have. Let's see what we have.

313
00:28:52,279 --> 00:28:57,182
A two of spades, three of
spades, four of diamonds,

314
00:28:57,617 --> 00:29:00,950
six of clubs, eight of spades.

315
00:29:01,154 --> 00:29:03,384
There isn't one worth a
jack in the whole bunch.

316
00:29:03,923 --> 00:29:05,584
Four of diamonds.

317
00:29:06,626 --> 00:29:10,562
- Hey, captain, what's that?
- Death cards.

318
00:29:10,764 --> 00:29:13,426
- What?
- Death cards.

319
00:29:13,633 --> 00:29:16,067
- Death?
- Lets Charlie know who did this.

320
00:29:20,206 --> 00:29:22,470
- Cheer up, son.
- We will not hurt or harm you.

321
00:29:22,676 --> 00:29:25,372
- Fire in the hole!
- Fire in the hole!

322
00:29:26,613 --> 00:29:29,173
We are here to help you.

323
00:29:31,718 --> 00:29:34,380
We are here to extend a welcome hand

324
00:29:34,587 --> 00:29:37,613
- Come on. Everybody in?
- To those who would like to return

325
00:29:37,824 --> 00:29:41,419
to the arms of the South
Vietnamese government.

326
00:29:42,295 --> 00:29:44,126
Get in. Hurry up.

327
00:29:46,433 --> 00:29:50,130
- Move it out.
- This is an area that is controlled

328
00:29:50,337 --> 00:29:52,305
by the Vietcong and North Vietnamese.

329
00:29:52,505 --> 00:29:55,804
Hey! Hey, what's this?

330
00:29:57,010 --> 00:29:58,773
What is this?

331
00:29:58,978 --> 00:30:01,037
This man's hurt pretty bad, sir.

332
00:30:01,247 --> 00:30:04,546
About the only thing that's holding
his guts in, sir, is that pot lid.

333
00:30:04,751 --> 00:30:07,185
Yeah? What do you have to say?

334
00:30:07,387 --> 00:30:09,582
This soldier is dirty VC.

335
00:30:09,789 --> 00:30:14,055
He wants water. He can drink paddy water.

336
00:30:14,260 --> 00:30:15,557
Get out of here! Give me
that. Give me that canteen.

337
00:30:17,836 --> 00:30:19,599
- He's VC.
- Any man that's brave enough to...

338
00:30:19,804 --> 00:30:22,329
Get out of here! I'll kick your fucking ass!

339
00:30:22,540 --> 00:30:24,201
He killed a lot of our people!

340
00:30:24,409 --> 00:30:27,105
Any man brave enough to fight
with his guts strapped on him

341
00:30:27,312 --> 00:30:28,973
can drink from my canteen any day.

342
00:30:29,180 --> 00:30:32,741
Hey, colonel, I think one of those
sailors is Lance Johnson, the surfer.

343
00:30:32,951 --> 00:30:34,213
Where? Here? You sure?

344
00:30:34,419 --> 00:30:35,977
Down there.

345
00:30:37,422 --> 00:30:39,014
Yeah? Here.

346
00:30:39,357 --> 00:30:42,417
Repeat, we have a body count. We have...

347
00:30:45,296 --> 00:30:46,923
What's your name, sailor?

348
00:30:47,132 --> 00:30:48,861
Gunner's Mate Third Class L. Johnson, sir.

349
00:30:49,067 --> 00:30:52,298
- Gunner's Mate Third Class...
- Hey. Lance Johnson, the surfer?

350
00:30:52,504 --> 00:30:53,994
Yes, sir.

351
00:30:54,272 --> 00:30:55,830
It's an honor to meet you, Lance.

352
00:30:56,041 --> 00:30:58,168
I've admired your nose riding for years.

353
00:30:58,376 --> 00:31:01,277
I like your cutback too. I think
you have the best cutback there is.

354
00:31:01,479 --> 00:31:04,039
- Thank you, sir.
- You can cut out the "sir" crap, Lance.

355
00:31:04,249 --> 00:31:06,114
I'm Bill Kilgore. I'm a goofy foot.

356
00:31:06,317 --> 00:31:08,285
- This guy with you?
- Yeah.

357
00:31:08,486 --> 00:31:10,147
I want you to meet some guys.

358
00:31:10,355 --> 00:31:12,118
- This is Mike from San Diego.
- Far out.

359
00:31:12,323 --> 00:31:13,415
Johnny from Malibu.

360
00:31:13,625 --> 00:31:14,956
- John, hi.
- Pretty solid surfers.

361
00:31:15,160 --> 00:31:16,650
- Far out.
- None of us are anywhere near

362
00:31:16,861 --> 00:31:18,852
- your class, though.
- No way.

363
00:31:19,064 --> 00:31:20,759
We do a lot of surfing around here, Lance.

364
00:31:20,965 --> 00:31:22,796
I like to finish operations early.

365
00:31:23,001 --> 00:31:25,492
Fly down to Vung Tau for the evening glass.

366
00:31:25,704 --> 00:31:28,002
Where you been riding, Lance?
Been riding since you got here?

367
00:31:28,206 --> 00:31:30,674
No way. I haven't surfed since I been here.

368
00:31:31,910 --> 00:31:34,811
- Through Christ, our Lord,
from whom all good things come.

369
00:31:35,013 --> 00:31:37,675
Through him in the unity of the Holy Spirit,

370
00:31:37,882 --> 00:31:41,010
all glory and honor is
yours, almighty Father.

371
00:31:41,219 --> 00:31:43,119
- Amen.
- Let us bring our iniquities

372
00:31:43,321 --> 00:31:45,585
to the Father in the
words our savior gave us.

373
00:31:45,790 --> 00:31:50,625
Our Father, who art in
heaven, hallowed be thy name.

374
00:31:50,829 --> 00:31:53,229
Thy kingdom come, thy will be done

375
00:31:53,431 --> 00:31:55,194
on earth as it is in heaven.

376
00:31:55,400 --> 00:31:57,925
Give us this day, our daily bread...

377
00:31:59,537 --> 00:32:02,301
- as we forgive those
who trespass against us,

378
00:32:02,507 --> 00:32:06,603
and lead us not into temptation,
but deliver us from evil.

379
00:32:15,887 --> 00:32:18,913
<i>Kilgore had had a pretty
good day for himself,</i>

380
00:32:19,124 --> 00:32:21,149
<i>They choppered in the T-bones and the beer</i>

381
00:32:21,359 --> 00:32:24,328
<i>and turned the LZ into a beach party,</i>

382
00:32:24,996 --> 00:32:27,658
<i>The more they tried to
make it just like home,</i>

383
00:32:27,866 --> 00:32:30,266
<i>the more they made everybody miss it,</i>

384
00:32:30,468 --> 00:32:34,564
Make my meat rare. Rare but not cold.

385
00:32:39,778 --> 00:32:43,077
<i>Well, he wasn't a bad officer, I guess,</i>

386
00:32:43,281 --> 00:32:46,717
<i>He loved his boys, and
you felt safe with him,</i>

387
00:32:46,918 --> 00:32:50,445
<i>He was one of those guys that
had that weird light around him,</i>

388
00:32:50,655 --> 00:32:53,749
<i>You just knew he wasn't gonna
get so much as a scratch here,</i>

389
00:32:53,958 --> 00:32:55,687
What happened to your mission, captain?

390
00:32:55,894 --> 00:32:58,089
Nha Trang forget all about you?

391
00:33:06,304 --> 00:33:08,101
Airborne.

392
00:33:09,107 --> 00:33:10,574
Sir,

393
00:33:10,775 --> 00:33:12,572
two places we can get into the river.

394
00:33:12,777 --> 00:33:15,473
- Yeah.
- Here and here.

395
00:33:15,680 --> 00:33:19,776
It's a pretty wide delta, but these are
the only two spots I'm really sure of.

396
00:33:20,819 --> 00:33:23,788
Well, that village you're pointing
at is kind of hairy, Willard.

397
00:33:23,988 --> 00:33:26,320
- What do you mean "hairy," sir?
- It's hairy.

398
00:33:26,524 --> 00:33:28,014
Got some pretty heavy ordnance.

399
00:33:28,226 --> 00:33:31,024
I lost a few recon ships
in there now and again.

400
00:33:31,229 --> 00:33:32,662
What's the name of that goddamn village?

401
00:33:32,864 --> 00:33:36,356
- Vin Drin Dop or Lop?
- Drop.

402
00:33:36,568 --> 00:33:39,537
Damn gook names all sound the same.

403
00:33:40,572 --> 00:33:43,803
Mike, you know anything about
this point at Vin Din Drop?

404
00:33:44,075 --> 00:33:45,440
That's a fantastic peak.

405
00:33:46,277 --> 00:33:48,177
- Peak?
- About 6 foot.

406
00:33:48,379 --> 00:33:52,042
It's an outstanding peak. It's got
both the long right and left slide,

407
00:33:52,250 --> 00:33:55,481
with a bowl section. It's
unbelievable. It's just tube city.

408
00:33:59,724 --> 00:34:01,589
Why didn't you tell me
that before? A good peak.

409
00:34:01,793 --> 00:34:04,353
There aren't any good peaks
in this whole shitty country.

410
00:34:04,562 --> 00:34:07,122
- It's all goddamn beach break.
- It's really hairy in there, sir.

411
00:34:07,332 --> 00:34:08,663
That's where we lost McDonald.

412
00:34:08,867 --> 00:34:12,769
They shot the hell out of us
there. That's Charlie's point.

413
00:34:14,072 --> 00:34:16,563
Sir, we can go in there tomorrow at dawn.

414
00:34:16,774 --> 00:34:19,106
There's always a good
offshore breeze in the morning.

415
00:34:19,310 --> 00:34:21,107
We may not be able to get the boat in.

416
00:34:21,312 --> 00:34:23,974
The draft at the mouth of
that river may be too shallow.

417
00:34:24,782 --> 00:34:27,683
We'll pick your boat up and put
it down right where you want it.

418
00:34:27,886 --> 00:34:30,480
This is the 1 st of the 9th, Air Cav, son.

419
00:34:30,688 --> 00:34:32,121
Airmobile.

420
00:34:32,523 --> 00:34:34,821
I can take that point and
hold it as long as I like.

421
00:34:35,026 --> 00:34:37,995
You can get anyplace up that river
that suits you, young captain.

422
00:34:38,196 --> 00:34:40,562
Hell, a 6-foot peak.

423
00:34:42,066 --> 00:34:44,227
All right, take a gunship
back to the division.

424
00:34:44,435 --> 00:34:46,460
Lance, go with Mike,
let him pick out a board.

425
00:34:46,671 --> 00:34:48,161
Bring me my Yater Spoon, the 8' 6".

426
00:34:48,373 --> 00:34:50,568
- I don't know, sir, it's...
- What is it, soldier?

427
00:34:50,775 --> 00:34:53,300
I mean, it's pretty hairy in
there. It's Charlie's point.

428
00:34:53,511 --> 00:34:55,570
Charlie don't surf!

429
00:35:19,804 --> 00:35:22,671
Hey, Jesus, Clean, you ain't
gonna believe this. Look.

430
00:35:23,808 --> 00:35:26,675
Hey, man. They're picking up the boat.

431
00:35:29,781 --> 00:35:31,146
How are you feeling, Jimmy?

432
00:35:31,349 --> 00:35:34,318
Like a mean motherfucker, sir!

433
00:35:35,820 --> 00:35:38,050
All right, son. Let her rip.

434
00:35:38,256 --> 00:35:39,985
Let's go.

435
00:37:02,607 --> 00:37:05,098
I never have got used to a light board.

436
00:37:05,309 --> 00:37:06,469
I can't get used to one.

437
00:37:06,677 --> 00:37:09,271
- I'm used to a heavy board.
- I know, it's a real drag.

438
00:37:09,480 --> 00:37:12,540
- You prefer a heavy or light board?
- Heavier.

439
00:37:12,750 --> 00:37:14,012
- Really?
- Yeah.

440
00:37:14,218 --> 00:37:16,379
I thought all the young
guys like lighter boards.

441
00:37:16,587 --> 00:37:18,384
You can't ride the nose on those things...

442
00:37:18,589 --> 00:37:20,181
<i>Big Duke Six, Big Duke Six,</i>

443
00:37:20,391 --> 00:37:22,222
This is Eagle Thrust 7. We got it spotted.

444
00:37:22,427 --> 00:37:25,157
Big Duke Six to Eagle
Thrust. Put on heading 2-7-0.

445
00:37:25,363 --> 00:37:26,921
Assume attack formation.

446
00:37:27,131 --> 00:37:29,895
<i>That's a roger, Big Duke,
Okay, we're going in,</i>

447
00:37:30,101 --> 00:37:31,068
Here we go.

448
00:37:31,269 --> 00:37:33,533
We'll come in low out of the rising sun

449
00:37:33,738 --> 00:37:36,263
and about a mile out, we'll put on the music.

450
00:37:36,474 --> 00:37:38,806
- Music?
- Yeah, I use Wagner.

451
00:37:39,010 --> 00:37:43,071
Scares the hell out of the
slopes. My boys love it.

452
00:37:43,281 --> 00:37:45,511
Hey, they're gonna play music.

453
00:37:51,923 --> 00:37:54,915
How come all you guys sit on your helmet?

454
00:37:55,693 --> 00:37:58,787
So we don't get our balls blown off.

455
00:38:10,274 --> 00:38:13,471
Big Duke Six to Eagle
Thrust. Put on psy-war- op.

456
00:38:13,678 --> 00:38:16,545
Make it loud. This is a Romeo Foxtrot.

457
00:38:16,747 --> 00:38:18,681
Shall we dance?

458
00:38:23,554 --> 00:38:25,249
Yes, sir.

459
00:40:43,861 --> 00:40:46,227
- Come on.
- All right, all right.

460
00:40:57,108 --> 00:40:59,440
<i>We got a couple characters at that tree line,</i>

461
00:40:59,644 --> 00:41:01,737
<i>We're taking fire from the holes,</i>

462
00:41:03,981 --> 00:41:05,005
Run, Charlie!

463
00:41:08,419 --> 00:41:10,785
<i>This should make everything down burn,</i>

464
00:41:23,301 --> 00:41:25,599
<i>We got a couple of people ahead here,</i>

465
00:41:25,803 --> 00:41:26,895
<i>What's going on down here?</i>

466
00:41:27,104 --> 00:41:28,765
<i>We got an automatic, Shoot to kill!</i>

